27/11/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The drug squad of the Greek police reported Friday (25 November) a significant rise in drug seizures during 2004, compared to previous years. It said authorities confiscated 1.15m kg of cocaine last year, with an estimated value of 9.2 billion euros -- a rise of almost 500 per cent compared to the previous year. Heroin seizures rose by 35 per cent to 334,000kg in 2004, the police said. (Kathimerini - 26/11/05) 
